Attribution
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project is an experimental re-implementation, in Vaadin Flow, of a slice of
RSSOwl / RSSOwlnix:

    RSSOwl       https://github.com/rssowl/RSSOwl
    RSSOwlnix    https://github.com/Xyrio/RSSOwlnix
    Copyright (c) 2005-2009 RSSOwl Development Team and contributors
    Licensed under the Eclipse Public License v1.0

The Vaadin code in poc/headlines/ was written independently against Vaadin Flow
APIs; it shares no source with RSSOwl. What is derived from RSSOwl is structural
and factual: a small number of behavioral constants (e.g. the 200-items-per-feed
retention cap).

In addition, poc/headlines/src/main/resources/default_feeds.xml is RSSOwl(nix)'s
own first-run default-subscriptions OPML, included VERBATIM from RSSOwlnix
(org.rssowl.ui/default_feeds.xml) under the Eclipse Public License v1.0, so that a
new user's feed tree mirrors the original application exactly. Its feed URLs are
RSSOwl's 2009-era list and are mostly defunct.

Should RSSOwl source be ported into this project in the future, the affected
files will carry the RSSOwl EPL-1.0 copyright header and be credited here.

